<p><br />Whanganui rider <strong>Seth Reardon</strong> rounds out the top five, while a see-saw battle has begun to develop in this year&rsquo;s New Zealand Enduro Championships, with two men now sharing the top spot in the premier grade.</p>
<p>Helensville&rsquo;s Tom Buxton won the first of seven rounds in the Yamaha and Mitas Tyres-backed series near Whangamata last month, with Cambridge rider Dylan Yearbury finishing runner-up, but those positions swapped around at round two near Porirua on Saturday.</p>
<p>Yearbury ruled the roost on the steep forestry course off Moonshine Road, Kapiti, edging out Buxton by just 16 seconds on the timing clocks.</p>
<p>That means, with both riders hogging the top two spots thus far, they share the bragging rights, although there is still a long way to go.</p>
<p>Third overall on the premier AA course on Saturday was Wainuiomata&rsquo;s Jake Whitaker, with Stratford&rsquo;s Josh Hunger and Whanganui&rsquo;s Seth Reardon completing the top five.</p>
<p><em>By Andy McGechan</em><br /><em>Motorcycling</em><br /><em>Whanganui Chronicle 10/4/19</em></p>
